beer.beer_description: This beauty pours a coppery brown, showcasing rich notes of freshly baked bread crust, toffee, and caramel, all complemented by zesty, sweet, and fruity undertones from the addition of bush honey. The Azacca hops introduce a subtle touch of wood and tropical fruit, adding depth without overpowering the natural sweetness. With mild carbonation, medium-light bitterness, and a smooth, easy-drinking body, this 5% ABV ale strikes a harmonious balance between flavour and refreshment.
